Overseer of Kaduna State Muslim Pilgrims Welfare Board, Malam Sani Dalhatu Musa is dead. The Nation learnt that, the Pilgrims board’s boss died in a ghastly motor accident along Kaduna-Abuja highway on Wednesday. Musa who became the Overseer of the Pilgrims’ board in January 2020 was the Head of Operations in the state Muslims Pilgrims Board. He had over 20 years’ experience on hajj operations. He was at various times a Pilgrim Officer in Birnin Gwari, Igabi and other local government areas of the state. He also held the position of a Zonal Coordinator, after which he became Head of Operations.‎